2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 87
BY SENATOR HODGES
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Lacie Thomas Fontenot for being named the 2026
Louisiana School Health Service Provider of the Year by the Louisiana Department of
Education.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Lacie Thomas Fontenot for being named the 2026 Louisiana School Health
3 Service Provider of the Year by the Louisiana Department of Education.
4 WHEREAS, Lacie Fontenot is a state and nationally certified speech-language
5 pathologist, who has faithfully served students within Livingston Parish Public Schools for
6 more than twelve years; and
7 WHEREAS, throughout her tenure, Lacie Fontenot has provided exceptional speech
8 and language services to students in Livingston Parish, including at Live Oak Middle School
9 and Live Oak Junior High, helping countless young people develop the skills necessary to
10 communicate effectively and succeed academically and socially; and
11 WHEREAS, in recognition of her exemplary dedication and impact, Lacie Fontenot
12 has been honored as the 2026 Louisiana School Health Service Provider of the Year by the
13 Louisiana Department of Education, a distinction that reflects both professional excellence
14 and meaningful contributions to student health and development; and
15 WHEREAS, through the School Health Provider of the Year program, the Louisiana
16 Department of Education recognizes and celebrates some of Louisiana's most exceptional
17 school health providers; and
18 WHEREAS, this program provides an opportunity to acknowledge providers who
