2 and
3 WHEREAS, Lacie Fontenot's service extends well beyond the traditional
4 responsibilities of a speech-language pathologist and demonstrates a deep and abiding
5 commitment to the school community; and
6 WHEREAS, she has taken a leadership role in organizing the Angel Tree project,
7 helping to provide Christmas gifts and support for students and families in need, all while
8 fostering a spirit of generosity and care within the school community; and
9 WHEREAS, Lacie Fontenot also dedicates her time overseeing the school's
10 self-sustained food pantry, working diligently to provide weekend food bags for students
11 facing food insecurity, and ensuring that basic needs are met so that students are better able
12 to focus on their education; and
13 WHEREAS, through her compassion, initiative, and unwavering dedication, Lacie
14 Fontenot exemplifies the highest ideals of public service and serves as a role model for
15 students, educators, and health service providers in the state.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
17 does hereby commend Lacie Thomas Fontenot on being named the 2026 Louisiana School
18 Health Service Provider of the Year and does hereby express sincere appreciation for her
19 outstanding contributions to the students and families of Livingston Parish and the state of
20 Louisiana.
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Lacie
22 Thomas Fontenot.
